What is 1e9? USED INSTEAD OF infinity
1e9 is a scientific notation representation of the number 1,000,000,000 (one billion).
It is a shorthand way to express large or very small numbers in a compact form. 

Which language uses 1e9?
The notation 1e9 is commonly used in several programming languages
C++ (which is the language in your code snippet)
Python
Java
JavaScript
Matlab
Ruby
In general, most modern programming languages support scientific notation (also called exponential notation) to express floating-point numbers.
